<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-SUNS-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PROBLEMS IN LOW POST, SHOOTING UPSET AINGE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB YOUNG  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ Halfway through the NBA season, the Suns find
themselves sitting in eighth place in the Western Conference. And
if the playoffs began today, they'd just barely keep alive their
streak of playoff appearances, now at 10 years.
</P>
<P>
   It wasn't supposed to be this tough. The Suns lost  &UR; Antonio
 &UR; McDyess to free agency, but the acquisition of  &UR; Tom Gugliotta
figured to fill that void. But the Suns lack the depth they've had
in recent seasons, and they hit the halfway mark a game below the
.500 mark (12-13) after a 103-93 overtime loss to the Rockets on
Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought we'd have more wins at this point,'' said Suns Coach
 &UR; Danny Ainge. ``I didn't know the West was going to be as tough as
it is, and everybody in the West has stayed fairly healthy.''
</P>
<P>
   And it doesn't get any easier. Their April schedule is
murderous.
</P>
<P>
   ``I looked at that before the season, and I did not like what I
saw,'' Ainge said. ``No sense killing myself over that.''
</P>
<P>
   The Suns have struggled in large part because they lack the
inside game most expected them to have with the addition of
Gugliotta and center  &UR; Luc Longley, and they've had spotty shooting
from outside.
</P>
<P>
   ``I did not expect that,'' Ainge said. ``I didn't think we would
have so much trouble scoring in the low post, or having such a
difficult time defending in the low post. That's like the blocking
and tackling of basketball _ scoring inside, rebounding and
defending inside.
</P>
<P>
   ``But I think in the second half of the season, we'll get better
at all of those things, and we'll get better as a team.'' &QL; 
It's an outrage &QL; 
 &UR; Charles Barkley of the Rockets was in a more jovial mood Saturday
night than he had been in Phoenix, when the Suns beat the Rockets.
</P>
<P>
   Suns reserve center  &UR; Joe Kleine defended Barkley down the
stretch in that game, and Barkley made only two of eight shots in
the final quarter.
</P>
<P>
   ``I called Joe (Friday) night _ in the middle of the night,''
Barkley said, gleefully. ``And I called him again this morning. I
told him it's been embarrassing to be walking around knowing he
actually stopped me in a game.'' &QL; 
Show me the money &QL; 
Barkley also took a playful swipe at teammate  &UR; Scottie Pippen, who
complained after that loss in Phoenix that he wasn't an integral
enough part of the Houston offense.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm disappointed in Scottie,'' Barkley said, raising his voice
so it carried throughout the locker room. ``He's bitching about
shots. He wants all the money AND all the shots. I'll take a switch
on that. He can have all the shots if I can have HALF his money.''
</P>
<P>
   Barkley is playing this season for $1 million. Pippen is getting
about $9 million in the first year of a seven-year contract. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-21-99 0015EST &QL; 
