<HEADLINE>
BRASWELL A CANDIDATE AT WASHINGTON STATE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS BRANAM  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Cal State Northridge head men's basketball coach Bobby Braswell
confirmed Saturday he is a candidate for the head job at Washington
State.
</P>
<P>
   Braswell met with Washington State athletic director Rick
Dickson on Thursday about the opening created when Kevin Eastman
resigned on March 10.
</P>
<P>
   ``Yeah, definitely,'' Braswell responded when asked if he was a
candidate. ``I'm listening. I was contacted by (Dickson) . . .
that's all I can really say.''
</P>
<P>
   Braswell just finished his third season at CSUN and led the
Matadors to a 17-12 record. It was the first winning record
produced by the Matadors under Braswell, who is 43-43 overall.
</P>
<P>
   Braswell came to CSUN, his alma mater, in 1996. He was
previously an assistant at Oregon and Long Beach State and head
coach at Cleveland High in the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
   Braswell was named as a candidate for the job Friday by the
Spokane Spokesman-Review, along with Oregon assistant Don Newman,
Kentucky assistant George Felton and Utah assistant Donny Daniels.
</P>
<P>
   Newman, a former head coach at Arizona State, appears to be the
front-runner, but Braswell and Daniels are both attractive
candidates. Daniels has been at Utah for nine years and is the
Utes' lead recruiter.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
