<P>
   COXNET FOCUS 0319: HAITI FUTURE _ Five years from now, U.S. aid
officials envision a very different Haiti. They see a place where
elections draw a majority of voters, and the average woman bears
only four children; a place where mayors provide garbage pick-up,
and tourists swarm seaside cities. But they've had these kinds of
visions before, however. (Emling, Cox Washington Bureau) Art
includes a 3-column color photo of two girls in a Haitian classroom
and a 1-column photo of a class of students listing to a radio
broadcast of the lessons.
</P>
