<P>
   HAITI SCHOOL _ Here, in the hemisphere's poorest country, where
many handicapped children are effectively written off at birth, is
St. Vincent's School for Handicapped Children. It's the only place
in Haiti designed to care for disabled young people, be they blind,
deaf or missing limbs. (Emling, Cox Washington Bureau) A 1-column
color photo of a handicapped girl waiting to be served her lunch at
a school for the handicapped.
