   DINGELL-PROFILE (Washington) _ Debbie Dingell, political spouse
extraordinaire, takes involvement with her mate's professional
institution to special levels, with the bipartisan civility retreat
for House members a prime example. Mrs. Dingell helped organize it.
Her husband, Rep. John Dingell, a Michigan Democrat who is the
House's most senior member, thinks the whole thing is bunk. But
that's only the beginning of their tensions: Mrs. Dingell wants to
take a position in the vanguard for gun control, while Dingell is a
former board member of the NRA. By Frank Bruni.
