<P>
   KOSOVO-U.S. (Washington) _ The Clinton administration on Sunday
dispatched a special envoy, Richard Holbrooke, to meet with
President Slobodan Milosevic of Yugoslavia in what senior officials
described as a final effort to persuade him to accept a peace
agreement for Kosovo and avoid a NATO bombing. By Jane Perlez.
