<HEADLINE>
GODS AND MONSTERS ... AND GIANTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Let 'em give out Oscars.
</P>
<P>
   We've got a deli case full o' Oscar Mayers _ for the biggest
sports 'dogs who couldn't help themselves and took a prominent role
in a motion picture that some actually paid to see in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   First, we respect Ray Allen 's performance too much in ``He Got
Game'' to include him in consideration here. This was no Alex
English. And the Spike Lee flick coulda flopped but instead made us
forget all about ``Cornbread, Earl and Me.''
</P>
<P>
   We coulda picked on Howie Long , but his picture deal with Fox
shows he means biz-ness. And his slushy scenes with co-star Suzy
Amis in ``Firestorm'' will only help now that Amis is shacked up
with director James ``Titanic'' Cameron . (In Hollywood, it's not
so much who you swap spit with on the screen, but who they're
swapping spit with off the screen.)
</P>
<P>
   And too bad that Superhero Shaq , who had a forgetful cameo in
``He Got Game,'' didn't follow up ``Steel'' with anything. He got
wise.
</P>
<P>
   Naw, for the biggest wiener-gone-loser of '98, the Oscar Mayer
goes to...
</P>
<P>
   Gheorghe Muresan in Billy Crystal 's career-ending ``My Giant.''
Crystal plays a Hollywood agent who stumbles on Max (Muresan) in
Romania and tries to get him into movies. Talk about art imitating
life.
</P>
<P>
   And because Gheorghe of the Jungle messed up the arches in his
feet during the shoot, he shot his NBA career in the foot. All he
could get after that was a role (uncredited) of a giant Spanish
soldier in ``The Mask of Zorro.''
</P>
<P>
   Today, he can't even get a casting call, let alone a
three-second call. What a giant lapse in judgment.
</P>
<P>
   _And how John Madden finds time to direct ``Shakespeare in
Love'' and do NFL games is beyond logic....
</P>
<P>
   _There's got to be some Academy recognition for Bob ``Don't call
me Robert Quinlan'' Costas , who, after the cheek-pinching cute
portrayal as himself in ``BASEketball,'' came out and ragged on the
stupidity of the movie. He couldn't see that going in? At least
fellow thespians Al Michaels , Jim Lampley , Bret Lewis and Tim
McCarver refrained from such pettiness....
</P>
<P>
   _ Bob ``I said don't call me Robert Quinlan'' Costas
</P>
<P>
   is more in his element tonight as a contestant on ``Jeopardy!''
(Channel 7, 7 p.m.), beating the smarty pants off co-celebs
</P>
<P>
   Robin Roberts and Keith Olbermann ....
</P>
<P>
   _And, finally, a happy 47th b-day today to Bob ``If you call me
Robert Quinlan one more time I'll sue, and don't call me diminutive
either'' Costas , who's now No.2 behind
</P>
<P>
   Billy Barty in oldest-living ``little person.''...
</P>
<P>
   _Postscript to the DiMaggio-Monroe marriage of superstar
athlete-actress: We missed Andre Agassi and ``Garth'' Brooke
Shields . Mainly because who thinks of Agassi as an athlete or
Shields as an actress anymore?...
</P>
<P>
   _A marketing group in Minnesota announced plans to start an NBA
``Legends Tour,'' a 30-game series of exhibitions featuring guys
like James Worthy, Michael Cooper and Spencer Haywood . ( Norm
Nixon must still be rehabbing that torn ACL from the last
``Legends'' appearance).
</P>
<P>
   Don't we have enough out-of-shape tall guys playing in the
regular NBA, or do attendance figures indicate there's a thirst for
this?...
</P>
<P>
   _Can't help it, but every time we see the guy in the Lakers
No.41 jersey spot up 30 feet out, we're about to scream: ``Don't
shoot that, Elden!''...
</P>
<P>
   _Why it matters how many teams from a conference are invited to
the NCAA Tournament _ each game a school plays, it receives
$170,000, no matter what round. And the cash is split among the
conference reps. So the 'Zags pull in $680,000, and WCC partners
Pepperdine and LMU make a nice chunk of change for doing
nuthin'....
</P>
</TEXT>
