<HEADLINE>
ACCOUNTS AND PEOPLE IN THE ADVERTISING WORLD 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Conn., Ill., Ohio, Minn., N.J., Ind.)  (lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MacManus Creating New Marketing Unit
</P>
<P>
   MacManus Group is creating a relationship marketing division in
New York, Dialogue Works, by consolidating Ayer/Deare &AMP; Partners in
New York, the relationship marketing division of N.W. Ayer &AMP;
Partners, with two accounts and 25 employees of Clarion Direct in
New Greenwich, Conn., part of Clarion Marketing and Communications.
</P>
<P>
   Dialogue Works will have billings estimated at $90 million from
clients like Kitchenaid, SBC Communications and Travelers
insurance. Bryan Dougherty, 40, and Trissie Rost, 41, will head
Dialogue Works as co-presidents, positions they held at Clarion
Direct.
</P>
<P>
   Bank One Selects Deutsch
</P>
<P>
   Bank One Corp. in Chicago and Columbus, Ohio, has named Deutsch
Inc. in New York to handle advertising, which had been handled by
the Martin Agency in Richmond, Va., a unit of Interpublic Group of
Cos. Billings were estimated at $60 million.
</P>
<P>
   The decision came after a review, managed by Bedford Group in
Atlanta, that had been narrowed to finalists including Deutsch;
D'Arcy Masius Benton &AMP; Bowles Communications in New York, which is
owned by MacManus Group, and TBWA/Chiat/Day in New York, part of
the TBWA Worldwide unit of Omnicom Group. Deutsch has recent
experience in bank advertising, having handled the Bank of America
account before that bank merged with Nationsbank Corp. to form the
new BankAmerica Corp.
</P>
<P>
   Service Campaign Will Feature Hanks
</P>
<P>
   The actor Tom Hanks, featured in the World War II film ``Saving
Private Ryan,'' has agreed to appear in his first public-service
campaign, to raise funds for a World War II memorial to be built in
Washington.
</P>
<P>
   The campaign is sponsored by the Advertising Council in New
York, which was founded in 1942 to stimulate War Bond sales and
increase support for the overall war effort. The council now
coordinates national public-service ad work.
</P>
<P>
   The campaign was created by Marsteller Advertising in New York,
part of Young &AMP; Rubicam Inc., and produced by Marsteller and a
sibling, Young &AMP; Rubicam Advertising. There will be television and
radio spots and print ads.
</P>
<P>
   Executive Joins Dugan Valva
</P>
<P>
   Keith McCracken, who in 1986 helped found the promotional
marketing shop McCracken Brooks in Minneapolis, is leaving to join
Dugan Valva Contess as executive vice president and general manager
for the Midwest and West.
</P>
<P>
   McCracken will oversee the account of the Pillsbury Co. unit of
Diageo PLC from the Minneapolis office of Dugan Valva, which is
based in Morristown, N.J. McCracken, 54, had been chairman at
McCracken Brooks, now owned by True North Communications.
</P>
<P>
   David Strandberg, chief creative officer at McCracken Brooks in
Minneapolis, said that he and Mark Lenss, chief executive, had no
immediate plans to name a new chairman.
</P>
<P>
   Accounts
</P>
<P>
   The Children's Place, West Caldwell, N.J., to Della Femina/Jeary
&AMP; Partners, New York, as the first agency to handle the account for
the children's apparel retailer. Billings were estimated at $7
million to $10 million.
</P>
<P>
   Kenra Inc., Indianapolis, to Young &AMP; Laramore, Indianapolis, as
the first agency to handle the account for the maker of hair-care
products. Billings were estimated at $2 million.
</P>
</TEXT>
