<P>
   Violence and a police crackdown marked the Kurdish New Year in
Turkey on Sunday with authorities arresting 1,500 people across the
country. Tension has already been running high in Turkey after a
surge of violent attacks blamed on Kurdish rebels seeking to avenge
the Feb. 15 capture of their leader, Abdullah Ocalan.
</P>
