 &UR; FROZEN HIGHWAY: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   During the coldest part of the tough winters in Canada's remote
Northwest Territories, when the crazy quilt of big lakes and small
ponds freezes, a few brave drivers take their trucks off the road
and onto a blue-ice highway that crosses 400 miles of bleached-out
tundra.
