<HEADLINE>
TORRE'S CANCER WAS CONTAINED  
(DW) 

</HEADLINE>
   c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAMPA, Fla. _ Joe Torre's cancer was confined to his prostate,
according to the results of pathology reports, the Yankees
announced Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The New York Yankees' manager had surgery Thursday to remove his
prostate, and the pathology tests show there is no trace of cancer
in the lymph nodes. More tests will be conducted in a month to
determine whether further treatment is necessary. Torre, operated
on in St. Louis, is expected to be released from the hospital this
week. He called Don Zimmer, the interim manager, at 6:30 Sunday
morning _ 5:30 in St. Louis _ to chat with him.
</P>
<P>
   The Yankees also have learned that thyroid cancer has been
diagnosed in Jaime Torres, a minor-league catcher. Torres, 28, will
have surgery soon, and doctors believe he will recover fully, after
missing six weeks.
</P>
</TEXT>
