<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    BEST SUPPORTING ACTOR
 &HT;    James Coburn, ``Affliction''
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ Character: Glen Whitehouse, Nick Nolte's abusive, alcoholic
father.
</P>
<P>
   _ Age: 70.
</P>
<P>
   _ Birthplace: Laurel, Neb.
</P>
<P>
   _ Oscar history: This is his first win and first nomination.
</P>
<P>
   _ Did you know? After working in TV commercials and small film
roles, he found fame in ``Our Man Flint'' (1966) and ``In Like
Flint'' (1967). His character _ swinging spy Derek Flint _ helped
inspire Mike Myers' Austin Powers character.
</P>
<P>
   _ Notable film roles: Bad guy Tex Panthollow in ``Charade''
(1963) with Audrey Hepburn; roles in ``The Magnificent Seven''
(1960), ``The Great Escape'' (1963), ``The Muppet Movie'' (1979)
and ``The Nutty Professor'' (1996).
</P>
<P>
   _ Quote: ``At my age, it's very rare that you get really good
parts. They throw us crumbs now that we really know how to do it.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Upcoming: No new roles lined up; has a small role in the
recent Mel Gibson thriller ``Payback.''
</P>
