<P>
   (NYT17) NEW YORK -- March 21, 1999 -- KERSHAW-HITLER, 3-21 --
Ian Kershaw, a British history professor, during a recent
interview. Kershaw, who has written a new biography of Adolph
Hitler, is the first to make full use of the diaries of Josef
Goebbels which were recently discovered in Moscow. Goebbels,
Hitler's minister of propaganda, portrays a formative Hitler prone
to bumbling and vacillation. (Thomas Dallal/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) NEW YORK -- March 21, 1999 -- RAVEL-OPERA-REVIEW, 3-21
-- Amy Burton and Kurt Ollmann sing the principal roles in
``L'Heure Espagnole,'' part of a Ravel double bill at the New York
City Opera. Both sing with great competence and occasionally with
real charm, and would have made an even better effect without the
self-referential smirks and slightly exaggerated gestures imposed
upon them. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) LOS ANGELES -- March 21, 1999 -- OSCARS-KAZAN, 3-21 --
Demonstrators against Elia Kazan getting a special Oscar carried
signs and shouted slogans before Sunday night's awards ceremony
outside the Dorothy Chandler Pavillion. (Monica Almeida/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
