BKC-DUKE-TEMPLE, 3-21 -- Head coach Mike Krzyzewski of the Duke
University Blue Devils after cutting down the net following Duke's
defeat over the Temple University Owls in the 1999 NCAA Division 1
Men's Basketball Championship East Regional Final game at the
Continental Airlines Arena. Duke defeated Temple 85-64 (Barton
Silverman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) NEWTON, Iowa -- March 21, 1999 -- ECON-SUSTAIN-1, 3-21
-- Workers use a large lazy susan to assemble washing-machine doors
at the Maytag assembly line. The system allows for a new door to be
assembled in 37 second, a marvel of productivity. Improvements in
workers' productivity helps to explain how despite a boombing
economy, inflation has not skyrocketed such as in previous years.
(Rodney White/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) PROVO, Utah -- March 21, 1999 -- PRIVACY-MARKETPLACE,
3-21 -- Michael Sheridan, vice president for strategic businesses
for Novell Corp., outside the company's office with Mount
Timpanogos in the background. Novell plans to announce on Monday an
Internet technology intended to give Web surfers greater control
over their identities as they travel through cyberspace. The
technology itself is Sheridan's brainchild. (Tim Kelly/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) NORTHWEST TERRITORIES -- March 21, 1999 --
CANADA-NORTH-4, 3-21 -- Trucks haul their cargo an ice highway in
the remote regions of Canada's northern territories recently.
During the coldest part of the tough winters in Canada's remote
Northwest Territories, when the crazy quilt of big lakes and small
ponds freezes, a few brave drivers take their trucks off the road
and onto a blue-ice highway that crosses 400 miles of bleached-out
tundra. (Anthony DePalma/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT10) NORTHWEST TERRITORIES -- March 21, 1999 --
