   Roberto Benigni
</P>
<P>
   ``Life Is Beautiful''
</P>
<P>
   _ Character: Guido Orefice, a comical Italian bookseller who
goes to great lengths to convince his young son that their
imprisonment in a World War II concentration camp is actually part
of a big game.
</P>
<P>
   _ Age: 46.
</P>
<P>
   _ Birthplace: Misericordia, Italy.
</P>
<P>
   _ Did you know? He's married to his ``Life Is Beautiful''
co-star Nicoletta Braschi. His father was a prisoner for two years
in a Nazi camp.
</P>
<P>
   _ Oscar history: This is his first win and nomination. He was
also nominated for best original screenplay.
</P>
<P>
   _ Other notable movies: ``Down by Law,'' ``Night on Earth,''
``Johnny Stecchino.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Upcoming: ``Asterix and Obelix vs. Caesar,'' co-starring
Gerard Depardieu.
</P>
