<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ENIGMATIC LAKERS ROLL INTO TOWN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICHIE WHITT 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ This is not your father's ``Showtime''
Lakers that roll into town tonight to play the Mavericks.
</P>
<P>
   Call this version ``Team Tabloid.''
</P>
<P>
   If it's not Shaquille O'Neal and Kobe Bryant arm wrestling for
control of the team, it's the controversial acquisition of Glen
Rice. It's firing ordained minister Del Harris while courting
cross-dressing power forward Dennis Rodman. It's 66-year-old, blue
jeans-wearing owner Jerry Buss trying to lift his team to an NBA
championship for the first time in 11 years while finding time to
bring girlfriends half his age into the postgame locker room.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers aren't the league's best team, but they are the most
talented. Their story lines are much more fascinating than their
layup lines, lifting ticket sales and fan interest while lowering
moral standards.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we're good for the NBA,'' Lakers guard Kobe Bryant
said. ``People either love us or hate us, but they seem to care a
heck of a lot about what happens either way.''
</P>
<P>
   LA struts into Dallas predictably enigmatic.
</P>
<P>
   They have surrendered 100 points in four of five games, but have
a chance to earn a 3-3 road trip with a victory tonight after
rallying from 24 points down to win in Orlando yesterday. The
Lakers have the league's best center in O'Neal, one of the best
shooting guards in Bryant and one of the best pure shooters in
Rice.
</P>
<P>
   The focus, however, is on Rodman.
</P>
<P>
   After an eight-day sabbatical that he attributes to neither
drinking, gambling or marital problems, Rodman returned yesterday,
apparently to stay.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm back, and I'm here to stay for good,'' Rodman said. ``I
had to find out if I wanted to play basketball. People have to
understand that I have to do these things. If not, they can just
tear up my contract and I'll leave.''
</P>
<P>
   After wavering for weeks on whether to pursue the 37-year-old
with a wall full of championship and rebounding skins, the Lakers
suddenly, sadly rely on him. Because LA traded backup center Elden
Campbell and waived Corie Blount to get Rice, Rodman's rebounding
and low-post defense is crucial to the team's title equation.
</P>
<P>
   During Rodman's absence _ rumored to be a trip to retain wife
Carmen Electra from the courtship of Motley Crue drummer Tommy Lee
_ the Lakers didn't play interior defense, they didn't rebound and
they didn't win.
</P>
<P>
   With Rodman the Lakers are 10-0; without him they are 8-9.
</P>
<P>
   ``We know we're rolling the dice a little,'' general manager
Mitch Kupchak said recently. ``But obviously what Dennis gives us
on the floor could pay huge dividends.''
</P>
<P>
   Rodman scored four points, grabbed six rebounds and picked up a
technical foul for throwing an elbow against the Magic. He says his
personal problems are fixed and that he'll stay with the team
through the season.
</P>
<P>
   LA, a fragile team walking the tightrope between greatness and
disaster, better hope so. With Rodman, the Lakers are a deep,
veteran team with the talent and savvy to be the favorites to win
the championship. Without him, they degenerate into a team with a
rookie coach, an impatient and eccentric owner, a 20-year-old
taking key shots and a dominating big man guaranteed to miss
crunch-time free throws.
</P>
<P>
   An NBA title that for years rested on the play of a man who
wagged his tongue may be in the hands of a talented misfit who
wears floppy Dr. Seuss hats.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
